Code Samples - Domain-Driven Design

This directory contains all code samples from the Domain-Driven Design course, organized by programming language for easy navigation and learning.

üìö Available Languages

C# (.NET)

  • Framework: .NET with xUnit and Moq
  • Samples: 13 comprehensive examples including entities, value objects, services, and testing
  • Features: Rich domain models, comprehensive unit testing, dependency injection
  • File Format: Markdown files with embedded C# code examples
  • View C# Samples ‚Üí

Java

  • Framework: Java with JUnit 5 and Mockito
  • Samples: 4 focused examples covering core DDD concepts
  • Features: BigDecimal for precision, strong typing, enterprise patterns
  • File Format: Markdown files with embedded Java code examples
  • View Java Samples ‚Üí

TypeScript

  • Framework: TypeScript with strong typing
  • Samples: 2 examples demonstrating type-safe domain modeling
  • Features: Type safety, access modifiers, module system
  • File Format: Markdown files with embedded TypeScript code examples
  • View TypeScript Samples ‚Üí

Python

  • Framework: Python 3.8+ with dataclasses and type hints
  • Samples: 2 examples showing Pythonic DDD patterns
  • Features: Dataclasses, Decimal precision, clean syntax
  • File Format: Markdown files with embedded Python code examples
  • View Python Samples ‚Üí

üéØ Learning Paths

For Beginners

Start with any language you're comfortable with:

  1. Choose Your Language: Pick C#, Java, TypeScript, or Python
  2. Start with Entities: Learn basic domain modeling
  3. Move to Value Objects: Understand immutability and validation
  4. Explore Services: Learn complex business operations
  5. Study Testing: Understand how DDD improves testability

For Intermediate Developers

Compare implementations across languages:

  1. Pick Your Primary Language: Start with your strongest language
  2. Study Advanced Patterns: Focus on services and testing
  3. Compare Languages: See how different languages express DDD concepts
  4. Explore Testing: Learn testing best practices and anti-patterns

For Advanced Developers

Focus on patterns and best practices:

  1. Cross-Language Study: Compare implementations across all languages
  2. Testing Patterns: Study comprehensive testing examples
  3. Best Practices: Learn domain modeling best practices
  4. Anti-Patterns: Understand what to avoid

üîó Navigation Structure

Each code sample includes:

  • Section Reference: Link back to the specific section in the main documentation
  • Previous/Next Navigation: Easy movement between samples
  • Key Concepts: Detailed explanation of what the code demonstrates
  • Related Concepts: Links to related samples and documentation
  • Language-Specific Features: How the language's features support DDD

üí° Key Learning Objectives

By studying these samples, you'll learn:

  1. Domain Entities: How to model business concepts with identity
  2. Value Objects: Creating immutable, self-validating objects
  3. Domain Services: Handling complex business operations
  4. Module Organization: Structuring domain code effectively
  5. Unit Testing: Testing domain logic with modern frameworks
  6. Best Practices: Avoiding common pitfalls and following good patterns
  7. Language Comparison: How different languages express DDD concepts

üöÄ Getting Started

  1. Read the Main Introduction: Start with 1-introduction-to-the-domain.md
  2. Choose Your Language: Pick the language you're most comfortable with
  3. Follow the Learning Path: Use the learning path that matches your experience level
  4. Study the Code: Each sample includes detailed explanations and context
  5. Practice: Try implementing similar patterns in your own projects
  6. Compare Languages: Explore how other languages implement the same concepts
